[[ja:御友別]]

'''Mitomowake''' (御友別), also known as '''Kibi no Mitomowake''' (吉備 御友別), is an ancient figure of [[Japan]] mentioned in texts such as the {{ill|Nihon Shoki|ja|日本書紀}}. He is considered an ancestor of the {{ill|Kibi clan|ja|吉備氏}}.{{Sfn|御友別（古代氏族）|2010年}}

== Genealogy ==
The {{ill|Nihon Sandai Jitsuroku|ja|日本三代実録}}, entry for the 22nd day of the 10th month of Genkei 3 (879), identifies Mitomowake as the second son of {{ill|Kibi no Takehiko|ja|吉備武彦}}.{{Sfn|御友別（古代氏族）|2010年}}

The {{ill|Shinsen Shōjiroku|ja|新撰姓氏録}}, entry for the Kibi no Omi lineage in the Imperial branch of the Right Capital, describes Mitomowake as the grandson of {{ill|Wakatakehiko|ja|稚武彦命}}.{{Sfn|御友別（古代氏族）|2010年}}

{| class="wikitable" style="margin:0 auto;background:#ffffff;text-align:center;font-size:85%;"
