== Records ==
The [[:en:Nihon Shoki|Nihon Shoki]], entry for the 22nd year, 3rd month, 14th day of Emperor Ōjin's reign, states that Ani-hime, consort of the emperor, was allowed to return to Kibi. It also identifies her as the sister of Mitomowake, ancestor of the Kibi no Omi.{{Sfn|御友別（古代氏族）|2010th year }}

On the 22nd year, 9th month, 6th day of Emperor Ōjin's reign, the emperor visited the Yoshita Ashimorimiya Palace (believed to be near {{ill|Ashimori, Okayama|ja|岡山市足守|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ashimori, Okayama|qq=}}). During this visit, Mitomowake had his descendants serve as stewards. For this service, the emperor divided the Kibi Province among Mitomowake’s descendants as follows:{{Sfn|御友別（古代氏族）|2010th year }}
* Eldest son, Inahayawake - Given Kawashima. Ancestor of the Shimotsudo no Omi. Kawashima later became Asakuchi District, Bitchū Province.
* Second son, Nakahiko - Given Kamitsudo. Ancestor of the Kamitsudo no Omi and Kaya no Omi. Kamitsudo later became Kamitsudo District, Bizen Province.
* Ototo-hiko - Given Mino. Ancestor of the Mino no Omi. Mino later became Mino District, Bizen Province.
* Younger brother, Kamowake - Given Natsukage. Ancestor of the Kasuga no Omi. The exact location of Natsukage is unknown, possibly near Kasukabe City.
* Elder brother, Urakobiwake - Given Sonokori. Ancestor of the Sonon no Omi. Sonokori later became Sonokori in Bitchū Province.
* Sister, Ani-hime - Received Orihime.

These descendants are noted to remain in Kibi Province.{{Sfn|御友別（古代氏族）|2010th year }}

== Descendants ==
=== Individuals ===
The {{ill|Kuge Nenjū Gyōji|ja|Kugyō補任|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kuge Nenjū Gyōji|qq=}} identifies [[:en:Kibi no Makibi|Kibi no Makibi]] as a ninth-generation descendant of Mitomowake.{{Sfn|吉備御友別（国史）}}

Additionally, the [[:en:Nihon Sandai Jitsuroku|Nihon Sandai Jitsuroku]], entry for the 22nd day of the 10th month of Genkei 3 (879), records that Jinami of the Harima-based Innami no Omi clan was an 11th-generation descendant of Mitomowake. Jinami's lineage received the surname "Kasuga Ason."{{Sfn|吉備御友別（国史）}}

=== Clans ===
As stated, the [[:en:Nihon Shoki|Nihon Shoki]] describes Mitomowake as the ancestor of the Kibi no Omi.

In the [[:en:Shinsen Shōjiroku|Shinsen Shōjiroku]], the following clan is noted as his descendants:
* Right Capital, Imperial Lineage, Kibi no Omi - Descendants of Mitomowake, grandson of Wakatakehiko.

== Interpretations ==
While the [[:en:Nihon Shoki|Nihon Shoki]] describes the division of Kibi under Mitomowake, some scholars suggest that these traditions were formulated as late as the 7th century, citing the [[:en:Kojiki|Kojiki]] story of Emperor Nintoku and Kurohibime, daughter of the Kibi no Ama clan.{{Sfn|吉備御友別（国史）}}

Connections with the massive [[:en:Tsukuriyama Kofun (Okayama)|Tsukuriyama Kofun]] in Okayama City have also been examined.

