'''Mitomowake''' (御友別), also known as '''Kibi no Mitomowake''' (吉備 御友別), is an ancient figure of [[:en:Japan|Japan]] mentioned in texts such as the [[:en:Nihon Shoki|Nihon Shoki]]. He is considered an ancestor of the [[:en:Kibi clan|Kibi clan]].{{Sfn|御友別（古代氏族）|2010th year }}

== Genealogy ==
The [[:en:Nihon Sandai Jitsuroku|Nihon Sandai Jitsuroku]], entry for the 22nd day of the 10th month of Genkei 3 (879), identifies Mitomowake as the second son of {{ill|Kibi no Takehiko|ja|吉備武彦|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kibi no Takehiko|qq=}}.{{Sfn|御友別（古代氏族）|2010th year }}

The [[:en:Shinsen Shōjiroku|Shinsen Shōjiroku]], entry for the Kibi no Omi lineage in the Imperial branch of the Right Capital, describes Mitomowake as the grandson of {{ill|Wakatakehiko|ja|稚武彦命|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Wakatakehiko|qq=}}.{{Sfn|御友別（古代氏族）|2010th year }}

