'''Mitomowake''' (御友別), also known as '''Kibi no Mitomowake''' (吉備 御友別), is an ancient figure of {{ill|Japan|en|Japan|qid=Q17|lt=Japan|1=Japan}} mentioned in texts such as the {{ill|Nihon Shoki|en|Nihon Shoki|qid=Q813935|lt=Nihon Shoki|1=Nihon Shoki}}. He is considered an ancestor of the {{ill|Kibi clan|en|Kibi clan|qid=Q11412645|lt=Kibi clan|1=Kibi clan}}.{{Sfn|御友別（古代氏族）|2010th year }}

== Genealogy ==
The {{ill|Nihon Sandai Jitsuroku|en|Nihon Sandai Jitsuroku|qid=Q1052981|lt=Nihon Sandai Jitsuroku|1=Nihon Sandai Jitsuroku}}, entry for the 22nd day of the 10th month of Genkei 3 (879), identifies Mitomowake as the second son of {{ill|Kibi no Takehiko|ja|吉備武彦|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kibi no Takehiko|qq=}}.{{Sfn|御友別（古代氏族）|2010th year }}

The {{ill|Shinsen Shōjiroku|en|Shinsen Shōjiroku|qid=Q1045362|lt=Shinsen Shōjiroku|1=Shinsen Shōjiroku}}, entry for the Kibi no Omi lineage in the Imperial branch of the Right Capital, describes Mitomowake as the grandson of {{ill|Wakatakehiko|ja|稚武彦命|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Wakatakehiko|qq=}}.{{Sfn|御友別（古代氏族）|2010th year }}

